  "lesson": {
    "title": "Differentiation Rules",
    "body": "The power rule (d/dx[xⁿ] = nxⁿ⁻¹), product rule ((fg)' = f'g + fg'), and quotient rule ((f/g)' = (f'g - fg')/g²) form the core algebraic toolkit. The chain rule handles compositions: d/dx[f(g(x))] = f'(g(x))·g'(x), essential for any nested function. Key transcendental derivatives: d/dx[sin x] = cos x, d/dx[cos x] = -sin x, d/dx[eˣ] = eˣ, and d/dx[ln x] = 1/x."
  },
